        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 3:27PM CDT by NWS Nashville TN</headline>
        <description>At 326 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Crossville, moving north at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Pleasant Hill, Crossville, Lake Tansi, and Monterey.

This includes Interstate 40 between mile markers 303 and 319.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 500 PM CDT for
Middle Tennessee.</instruction>
